task_structure.input: Triage incoming tickets, auto-fix common issues, escalate complex cases to engineers, and track resolution metrics.

subtasks.input: Classify tickets based on issue type, severity, and urgency using predefined criteria.
Check categorized tickets against a database of known frequent issues requiring auto-fix.
Execute preconfigured automated solutions (e.g., password resets, account unlocks) for identified common issues.
Forward non-standard tickets to the appropriate engineering team with context and priority details.
Engineers diagnose and resolve complex issues through manual troubleshooting and fixes.
Mark tickets as resolved in the system after verification of successful auto-fix or engineer resolution.
Aggregate data on ticket resolution times, auto-fix success rates, and escalation frequencies from closed tickets.
Identify trends, bottlenecks, and areas for process improvement using collected metric data.
Compile insights and recommendations into a formal report for stakeholders.
